1 A BILL for an Act to amend and reenact section 48-01.2-05 of the North Dakota Century Code,
2 relating to contents of advertisement for public improvement projects.
3 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
4 SECTION 1. AMENDMENT. Section 48-01.2-05 of the North Dakota Century Code is
5 amended and reenacted as follows:
6 48-01.2-05. Contents of advertisement.
7 The advertisement for bids required by section 48-01.2-04 must state:
8 1. The nature of the work and the type and location of the proposed public improvement.
9 2. When and where the plans, drawings, and specifications may be seen and examined.
10 3. The place, date, and time the bids will be opened.
11 4. That each bid must be accompanied by a separate envelope containing the
12 contractor's license and bid security. The bid security must be in a sum equal to five
13 percent of the full amount of the bid and must be in the form of a bidder's bond. A
14 bidder's bond must be executed by the bidder as principal and by a surety, conditioned
15 that if the principal's bid is accepted and the contract awarded to the principal, the
16 principal, within ten days after notice of the award, shall execute a contract in
17 accordance with the terms of the bid and the bid bond and any condition of the
18 governing body. A countersignature of a bid bond is not required under this section. If
19 a successful bidder does not execute a contract within the ten days allowed, the
20 bidder's bond must be forfeited to the governing body and the project awarded to the
21 next lowest responsible bidder.
22 5. That a bidder, except a bidder on a municipal, rural, and industrial water supply project
23 using funds provided under Public Law No. 99-294 [100 Stat. 426; 43 U.S.C. 390a],
24 must be licensed for the full amount of the bid as required by section 43-07-12. For
